ackground` | `story.generate_pitches` | `regenerate_pitches` | `StageOperationToolResult` | marks `pitches` in progress and refreshes downstream staleness |\ndocs/story-workflow-tool-registry.md:39:| `refine_pitch` | `pitches` | `background` | `story.refine_pitch` | `refine_pitch` | `StageOperationToolResult` | creates a linked refined pitch revision, selects it, and refreshes downstream planning |\ndocs/story-workflow-tool-registry.md:42:| `generate_beat_sheet` | `beats` | `background` | `story.generate_beat_sheet` | `refine_beat_sheet`, `regenerate_beat_sheet` | `StageOperationToolResult` | marks `beats` in progress and invalidates composition work |\ndocs/story-workflow-tool-registry.md:43:| `update_setup_heuristics` | `story_setup` | `direct` | `story.update_setup_heuristics` | `update_story_setup` | `UpdateSetupHeuristicsToolResult` | creates a selected `story_setups` revision, records user-edit and selection events, invalidates downstream stages, cancels active composition/audio jobs |\ndocs/story-workflow-tool-registry.md:44:| `compose_next_segment` | `composition` | `background` | `story.compose_next_segment` | `start_composition` | `CompositionToolResult` | cancels active composition jobs, creates a composition job, seeds a segment row, records initial progress |\ndocs/story-workflow-tool-registry.md:45:| `rewrite_segments` | `composition` | `background` | `story.rewrite_segments` | `start_composition`, `redirect_composition` | `CompositionToolResult` | cancels active composition jobs, creates a rewrite job, seeds a revised segment row, records initial progress |\ndocs/story-workflow-tool-registry.md:46:| `estimate_audio_length` | `audio` | `direct` | `story.estimate_audio_length` | `start_audio_generation` | `EstimateAudioLengthToolResult` | computes an estimate from composition segments or story-setup targets without mutating durable state |\ndocs/story-workflow-tool-registry.md:47:| `start_audio_generation` | `audio` | `background` | `story.start_audio_generation` | `start_audio_generation` | `StartAudioGenerationToolResult` | cancels active audio jobs, creates an audio job, records an estimate, marks `audio` in progress |\ndocs/story-workflow-tool-registry.md:118:The intent-parser prompt still emits chat actions, but it now also receives a serialized summary of\ndocs/story-workflow-tool-registry.md:125:- [`backend/app/ai/prompts/intent_parser.md`](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/app/ai/prompts/intent_parser.md)\ndocs/story-workflow-tool-registry.md:133:5. Add tests for registry listing, direct execution, worker dispatch, and prompt exposure if the tool is LLM-facing.\nfrontend/src/features/session/chat/actionEchoes.ts:113:  if (selectionKind === 'pitch') {\nfrontend/src/features/session/chat/actionEchoes.ts:115:      ? `Selected pitch: ${label}. ${rationale}`\nfrontend/src/features/session/chat/actionEchoes.ts:116:      : `Selected pitch: ${label}`\nfrontend/src/features/session/chat/actionEchoes.ts:121:      ? `Selected character sheet: ${label}. ${rationale}`\nfrontend/src/features/session/chat/actionEchoes.ts:122:      : `Selected character sheet: ${label}`\nfrontend/src/features/session/chat/actionEchoes.ts:126:    return `Accepted beat sheet: ${label}`\nfrontend/src/features/session/chat/actionEchoes.ts:202:  if (outputKind === 'pitch_batch') {\nfrontend/src/features/session/chat/actionEchoes.ts:204:      return `Generated ${countLabel}pitch options. ${summary}`\nfrontend/src/features/session/chat/actionEchoes.ts:207:    return `Generated ${countLabel}pitch options.`\nfrontend/src/features/session/chat/actionEchoes.ts:212:      return `Generated ${countLabel}character sheets. ${summary}`\nfrontend/src/features/session/chat/actionEchoes.ts:215:    return `Generated ${countLabel}character sheets.`\nfrontend/src/features/session/chat/actionEchoes.ts:233:    case 'regenerate_pitches':\nfrontend/src/features/session/chat/actionEchoes.ts:234:      return 'refresh the pitch options'\nfrontend/src/features/session/chat/actionEchoes.ts:235:    case 'refine_pitch':\nfrontend/src/features/session/chat/actionEchoes.ts:236:      return 'refine the selected pitch'\nfrontend/src/features/session/chat/actionEchoes.ts:237:    case 'select_pitch':\nfrontend/src/features/session/chat/actionEchoes.ts:238:      return 'change the selected pitch'\nfrontend/src/features/session/chat/actionEchoes.ts:240:      return 'change the character sheet'\nfrontend/src/features/session/chat/actionEchoes.ts:242:      return 'refine the character sheet'\nfrontend/src/features/session/chat/actionEchoes.ts:244:      return 'refresh the character sheet'\nfrontend/src/features/session/chat/actionEchoes.ts:246:      return 'accept the beat sheet'\nfrontend/src/features/session/chat/actionEchoes.ts:248:      return 'refine the beat sheet'\nfrontend/src/features/session/chat/actionEchoes.ts:250:      return 'refresh the beat sheet'\nfrontend/src/features/session/chat/actionEchoes.ts:253:    case 'start_composition':\nfrontend/src/features/session/chat/actionEchoes.ts:254:      return 'start composition'\nfrontend/src/features/session/chat/actionEchoes.ts:259:    case 'redirect_composition':\nfrontend/src/features/session/chat/actionEchoes.ts:260:      return 'redirect composition'\nfrontend/src/features/session/chat/actionEchoes.ts:261:    case 'update_audio_settings':\nfrontend/src/features/session/chat/actionEchoes.ts:262:      return 'update audio settings'\nfrontend/src/features/session/chat/actionEchoes.ts:263:    case 'start_audio_generation':\nfrontend/src/features/session/chat/actionEchoes.ts:264:      return 'start audio generation'\nfrontend/src/features/session/chat/actionEchoes.ts:347:  const evaluation = result.policy_evaluation\nfrontend/index.html:9:      content=\"Storyteller is a calm studio for crafting bedtime stories from first idea to finished narration.\"\ndocs/adr/0001-core-runtime-architecture.md:8:Storyteller is a session-based bedtime story studio, not a single-shot prompt demo. A user needs to move through a staged workflow, leave, come back later, and still see the current plan, generated text, generated audio, and recent activity.\ndocs/adr/0001-core-runtime-architecture.md:12:- the browser cannot hold Gemini credentials or call provider APIs directly\ndocs/adr/0001-core-runtime-architecture.md:14:- composition and audio generation are too slow and failure-prone to run inside request threads\ndocs/adr/0001-core-runtime-architecture.md:18:This ADR records the first architecture decisions that later prompts should assume unless another ADR replaces them.\ndocs/adr/0001-core-runtime-architecture.md:24:All Gemini text, planning, composition, and narration calls belong behind backend-owned adapters and services.\ndocs/adr/0001-core-runtime-architecture.md:29:- The backend policy layer decides whether a model-suggested action is valid for the current workflow stage before state changes are accepted.\ndocs/adr/0001-core-runtime-architecture.md:35:At minimum, later prompts should treat these as first-class durable records:\ndocs/adr/0001-core-runtime-architecture.md:41:- brief, pitch batch, selected pitch\ndocs/adr/0001-core-runtime-architecture.md:42:- character sheet candidates and selection\ndocs/adr/0001-core-runtime-architecture.md:43:- beat sheet\ndocs/adr/0001-core-runtime-architecture.md:45:- composition jobs and segment progress\ndocs/adr/0001-core-runtime-architecture.md:46:- audio jobs and segment progress\ndocs/adr/0001-core-runtime-architecture.md:56:- Story exports, intermediate composition files, narration segments, and final audio artifacts live in object storage.\ndocs/adr/0001-core-runtime-architecture.md:63:The browser needs live updates during composition and audio generation, and those updates need to remain tied to durable backend state.\ndocs/adr/0001-core-runtime-architecture.md:73:Composition and audio generation run in a worker process that is separate from the API process.\ndocs/adr/0001-core-runtime-architecture.md:76:- Workers claim pending jobs, call Gemini or narration providers, persist partial outputs, and append durable events.\ndocs/adr/0001-core-runtime-architecture.md:77:- The API remains responsible for request handling, policy checks, and websocket fan-out.\ndocs/adr/0001-core-runtime-architecture.md:85:- They guide pitch generation, beat planning, and composition prompts.\ndocs/adr/0001-core-runtime-architecture.md:87:- They should not be enforced as exact cutoffs that distort story quality or bedtime tone.\ndocs/adr/0001-core-runtime-architecture.md:89:The product should prefer a coherent, calm bedtime story over exact numeric compliance. If the system misses a target, it should do so transparently and gracefully rather than by truncating or padding the story unnaturally.\ndocs/adr/0001-core-runtime-architecture.md:99:- Later prompts have a clear split between API responsibilities and worker responsibilities.\ndocs/adr/0001-core-runtime-architecture.md:104:- Websocket delivery and worker orchestration add coordination work that later prompts must implement carefully.\ndocs/adr/0001-core-runtime-architecture.md:113:- If a later prompt needs to change any of these choices, record the override in a new ADR instead of silently drifting.\nbackend/tests/test_health.py:23:            \"storyteller-sessions, storyteller-audio, storyteller-exports at \"\ndocs/contributing.md:24:- Prefer names that describe product concepts directly: `session`, `pitch`, `beat_sheet`, `audio_job`.\ndocs/contributing.md:45:- Keep AI-produced runtime assets, exported documents, and generated audio in backend-managed storage locations instead of checking them into git.\ndocs/domain-model.md:11:- Composition and audio are long-running workflows backed by durable records, not one-shot request responses.\ndocs/domain-model.md:16:The session snapshot returned to the UI should eventually include these fields, even if some land in later prompts:\ndocs/domain-model.md:28:| `selected_pitch_id` | Accepted pitch record. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:32:| `active_composition_job_id` | Current composition job, if writing or rewrite work is running. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:33:| `active_audio_job_id` | Current audio job, if narration work is running. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:35:| `latest_audio_asset_id` | Most recent playable final audio artifact. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:41:such as pitches, character sheets, beat sheets, and setup revisions point back to the owning\ndocs/domain-model.md:49:| `story_session` | Root aggregate for one bedtime-story project. | IDs, title, stage pointers, overall status, timestamps. | Owns the current accepted choices and job pointers. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:51:| `genre` | Curated genre catalog entry. | slug, label, description, bedtime-safety notes, arc notes. | Backend-owned reference data. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:52:| `tone_profile` | Curated tone option linked to a genre. | `genre_id`, slug, label, descriptors, bedtime notes, default planning hints. | Tone choices are filtered by genre. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:54:| `pitch` | One candidate story premise. | batch or generation group, summary, hook, bedtime notes, selection flag. | `selected_pitch_id` on the session represents the accepted pitch; selection does not require a separate table. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:56:| `beat_sheet` | Structured Save-the-Cat plan. | ordered beats, bedtime-adaptation notes, revision. | Must be editable and versioned. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:58:| `composition_job` | Parent job record for writing or rewriting text. | status, progress, attempt count, stop reason, current segment pointer. | Not listed in the prompt title, but needed to make `composition_segment` durable and resumable. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:59:| `composition_segment` | One planned or written segment of the story. | segment index, planned summary, text, revision number, superseded segment, status. | Supports interruption, partial persistence, and rewrites of earlier sections. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:60:| `audio_job` | Parent job record for narration generation. | voice, speed, music setting, progress, status, compiled asset pointer. | Audio should be resumable and segment-aware. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:61:| `session_asset` | Durable artifact metadata for session files and exports. | asset kind, object path, MIME type, byte size, checksum, segment index, readiness status. | Covers draft snapshots, composition segments, audio segments, `.docx`, and final audio without scanning object storage. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:73:| 4 | `pitches` | Pitches | One pitch is accepted or the user intentionally keeps a current pitch set for further refinement. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:74:| 5 | `characters` | Characters | One character sheet is accepted. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:75:| 6 | `beats` | Beat sheet | One beat sheet is accepted. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:77:| 8 | `composition` | Composition | The current story text is complete enough to hand off to narration. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:78:| 9 | `audio` | Audio | Final narration assets are generated for the current story text and settings. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:95:| `in_progress` | Durable work is actively being produced or updated. | Pitch generation is running, composition is streaming segments, or audio rendering is underway. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:96:| `completed` | The stage has an accepted output that is still valid relative to all upstream dependencies. | A beat sheet was accepted and no upstream planning change has made it stale. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:97:| `needs_regeneration` | The stage was completed before, but an upstream change made its accepted output stale. The old output may remain visible for comparison, but it is not the current source of truth. | The user edits characters after a beat sheet exists, so beats, composition, audio, and finalize become stale. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:112:`genre -> tone -> brief -> pitches -> characters -> beats -> story_setup -> composition -> audio -> finalize`\ndocs/domain-model.md:131:| `genre` | `tone`, `brief`, `pitches`, `characters`, `beats`, `composition`, `audio`, `finalize` |\ndocs/domain-model.md:132:| `tone` | `brief`, `pitches`, `characters`, `beats`, `composition`, `audio`, `finalize` |\ndocs/domain-model.md:133:| `brief` | `pitches`, `characters`, `beats`, `composition`, `audio`, `finalize` |\ndocs/domain-model.md:134:| `pitches` | `characters`, `beats`, `composition`, `audio`, `finalize` |\ndocs/domain-model.md:135:| `characters` | `beats`, `composition`, `audio`, `finalize` |\ndocs/domain-model.md:136:| `beats` | `composition`, `audio`, `finalize` |\ndocs/domain-model.md:137:| `story_setup` | `composition`, `audio`, `finalize` |\ndocs/domain-model.md:138:| `composition` | `audio`, `finalize` |\ndocs/domain-model.md:139:| `audio` | `finalize` |\ndocs/domain-model.md:145:- They still influence later composition, but a new pitch or character sheet does not automatically erase the user's preferred target length.\ndocs/domain-model.md:151:- A composition job may move between `in_progress`, paused, resumed, or cancelled states without leaving the `composition` stage.\ndocs/domain-model.md:153:- A rewrite request against an earlier segment creates a new `composition_job` or new segment revision rather than mutating history in place.\ndocs/domain-model.md:155:- Any accepted composition rewrite marks `audio` and `finalize` as `needs_regeneration`.\ndocs/domain-model.md:156:- If the user decides the plan itself is wrong, they may navigate back to `beats` or `story_setup`, accept changes there, and let the backend mark `composition` and later stages stale.\ndocs/domain-model.md:163:   - Example: `genre`, `tone`, and `brief` are `completed`; `pitches` is `in_progress`.\ndocs/domain-model.md:164:   - Result: open the session on `resume_stage = pitches`.\ndocs/domain-model.md:166:   - Example: `composition`, `audio`, and `finalize` were `completed`, then the user edits the beat sheet.\ndocs/domain-model.md:167:   - Result: `composition`, `audio`, and `finalize` become `needs_regeneration`, and `resume_stage = composition`.\ndocs/domain-model.md:174:The repo does not yet have a generated cross-language schema package, so prompt 10 uses a boring mirrored-contract approach:\ndocs/domain-model.md:180:Rules for later prompts:\ndocs/domain-model.md:184:- If a later prompt introduces JSON Schema or code generation, generate from these same identifiers instead of renaming them.\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:340:              \"const\": \"composition\",\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:341:              \"default\": \"composition\",\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:346:              \"const\": \"composition.chunk\",\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:347:              \"default\": \"composition.chunk\",\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:552:            \"composition\",\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:553:            \"audio\"\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:1326:            \"pitches\",\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:1330:            \"composition\",\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:1331:            \"audio\",\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:1514:          \"composition.chunk\": \"#/$defs/CompositionChunkRealtimeEvent\",\nfrontend/src/features/session/chat/SessionChatPane.test.tsx:21:    body: 'Accepted pitch: Lanterns Over Juniper Lake.',\nfrontend/src/features/session/chat/SessionChatPane.test.tsx:52:      screen.getByText('Accepted pitch: Lanterns Over Juniper Lake.'),\nfrontend/src/features/session/chat/SessionChatPane.test.tsx:108:        disabledReason=\"The composer is paused while audio generation is active.\"\nfrontend/src/features/session/chat/SessionChatPane.test.tsx:119:        'The composer is paused while audio generation is active.',\nfrontend/src/features/session/chat/SessionChatPane.test.tsx:131:        activityLabel=\"One chat-requested pitch change is waiting for review.\"\nfrontend/src/features/session/chat/SessionChatPane.test.tsx:141:            title: 'Refine this pitch',\nf