pace.\"\nbackend/tests/test_session_service.py:1403:    assert \"invalidated pitches\" in stage_map[WorkflowStage.BRIEF].last_event_summary\nbackend/tests/test_session_service.py:1404:    assert \"invalidated pitches\" in stage_map[WorkflowStage.PITCHES].last_event_summary\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:3:This document defines the append-only event contract introduced in prompt 15.\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:29:| `selection.recorded` | Accepted or candidate selection for genre, tone, pitch, character sheet, beat sheet, or story setup. | `user` | stage-specific |\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:31:| `content.user_edit.recorded` | Structured user-authored edits to durable planning or composition records. | `user` | stage-specific |\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:34:| `composition.progress.recorded` | Durable composition job progress for replay and worker debugging. | `system` | `composition` |\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:35:| `audio.progress.recorded` | Durable narration job progress for replay and worker debugging. | `system` | `audio` |\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:57:  \"invalidated_stages\": [\"pitches\", \"characters\", \"beats\", \"composition\", \"audio\", \"finalize\"],\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:58:  \"current_stage\": \"pitches\",\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:59:  \"resume_stage\": \"pitches\",\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:75:  \"summary_text\": \"Updated beat sheet notes from the workspace.\"\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:96:- `record_composition_progress(...)`\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:97:- `record_audio_progress(...)`\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:128:event_log.record_composition_progress(\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:130:    job_id=composition_job.id,\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:152:  `summary_text` so later prompts, summaries, and chat replay can stay grounded\ndocs/architecture-overview.md:19:        +--> domain services and policy layer\ndocs/architecture-overview.md:21:        |         +--> AI adapters for planning, composition, and narration\ndocs/architecture-overview.md:25:        +--> background workers for composition and audio generation\ndocs/architecture-overview.md:31:## Why Gemini Calls Must Stay on the Backend\ndocs/architecture-overview.md:33:All Gemini access belongs on the server side for four reasons:\ndocs/architecture-overview.md:37:3. Durable orchestration: prompts, structured outputs, retries, and model selection need to be coordinated with persistent session data and job records.\ndocs/architecture-overview.md:38:4. Provider flexibility: keeping Gemini behind backend adapters lets the app keep a stable internal interface while model IDs, structured output tactics, or narration providers evolve.\ndocs/architecture-overview.md:47:- partial story text and audio segments need durable checkpoints\ndocs/architecture-overview.md:62:- `services/`: workflow logic and policy enforcement\ndocs/architecture-overview.md:63:- `ai/`: Gemini planning, composition, and narration adapters\ndocs/architecture-overview.md:64:- `worker/`: background job execution for writing and audio\ndocs/architecture-overview.md:77:- Pitch batch and selected pitch\ndocs/architecture-overview.md:78:- Character batch and selected character sheet\ndocs/architecture-overview.md:101:Background workers and most domain layers are still planned work. PostgreSQL and the file-backed GCS emulator are now available in the local Compose stack so later prompts can connect durable state and artifact storage without redefining the infrastructure contract.\ndocs/architecture-overview.md:103:Story setup preferences such as word count, runtime, and chapter count are planning hints rather than hard limits. The system should use them to guide prompts, estimates, and editing suggestions without forcing exact compliance at the expense of story quality or bedtime tone.\ndocs/system-diagram.md:3:This diagram shows the intended runtime shape for Storyteller after the core session, worker, and realtime prompts are built. It documents where session resume, durable event history, realtime delivery, and long-running jobs belong.\ndocs/system-diagram.md:8:    API[\"FastAPI API<br/>routes, policy checks, session reads/writes\"]\ndocs/system-diagram.md:10:    Worker[\"Worker process<br/>composition jobs, audio jobs, retries, interruption\"]\ndocs/system-diagram.md:12:    GCS[(\"File-backed GCS emulator<br/>story exports, audio segments,<br/>final artifacts\")]\ndocs/system-diagram.md:13:    Gemini[\"Gemini adapters<br/>planning, composition, narration\"]\ndocs/system-diagram.md:28:    Worker -->|\"planning, composition, TTS calls\"| Gemini\ndocs/system-diagram.md:29:    API -. \"backend-owned model config and policy\" .-> Gemini\ndocs/system-diagram.md:34:- The browser never calls Gemini directly.\ndocs/system-diagram.md:42:Word count, runtime, and chapter count are soft planning hints. They shape prompts and estimates, but the system should favor story quality, bedtime tone, and coherent pacing over exact numeric compliance.\nbackend/tests/test_pitch_generation_service.py:3:from app.ai.pitch_generation import PitchGenerationTransportError\nbackend/tests/test_pitch_generation_service.py:11:from app.services.pitch_generation import PitchGenerationService, build_pitch_model_output\nbackend/tests/test_pitch_generation_service.py:25:                pitches=[\nbackend/tests/test_pitch_generation_service.py:34:                            \"the bedtime journey into a longer night.\"\nbackend/tests/test_pitch_generation_service.py:53:                            \"bedtime mystery with fast emotional repair.\"\nbackend/tests/test_pitch_generation_service.py:68:                            \"stakes stay soft and bedtime-safe.\"\nbackend/tests/test_pitch_generation_service.py:87:        raise PitchGenerationTransportError(\"simulated Gemini outage\")\nbackend/tests/test_pitch_generation_service.py:104:                \"The child must stay calm while helping the harbor settle for bedtime.\"\nbackend/tests/test_pitch_generation_service.py:106:            why_it_fits=(\"It fits the selected lane by staying gentle and clearly bedtime-safe.\"),\nbackend/tests/test_pitch_generation_service.py:111:                pitches=[repeated, repeated, repeated]\nbackend/tests/test_pitch_generation_service.py:120:def test_eval_structured_pitch_generation_happy_path_uses_adapter_output() -> None:\nbackend/tests/test_pitch_generation_service.py:123:    result = service.generate_pitches(\nbackend/tests/test_pitch_generation_service.py:127:            \"bring each light home before bedtime.\"\nbackend/tests/test_pitch_generation_service.py:136:    assert [pitch.title for pitch in result.pitches] == [\nbackend/tests/test_pitch_generation_service.py:155:    result = service.generate_pitches(\nbackend/tests/test_pitch_generation_service.py:159:            \"bring each light home before bedtime.\"\nbackend/tests/test_pitch_generation_service.py:168:    assert len(result.pitches) == 4\nbackend/tests/test_pitch_generation_service.py:171:    assert result.raw_response[\"fallback_reason\"] == \"simulated Gemini outage\"\nbackend/tests/test_pitch_generation_service.py:177:    result = service.generate_pitches(\nbackend/tests/test_pitch_generation_service.py:191:def test_eval_pitch_model_output_preserves_provider_context_and_criteria() -> None:\nbackend/tests/test_pitch_generation_service.py:192:    result = PitchGenerationService(adapter=StubPitchGenerationAdapter()).generate_pitches(\nbackend/tests/test_pitch_generation_service.py:199:    model_output = build_pitch_model_output(result)\nbackend/tests/test_pitch_generation_service.py:203:    assert model_output[\"prompt_version\"] == \"pitch_generation.v2\"\nbackend/tests/test_pitch_generation_service.py:207:def test_eval_refinement_fallback_keeps_the_source_pitch_and_guidance_visible() -> None:\nbackend/tests/test_pitch_generation_service.py:208:    result = PitchGenerationService(adapter=FailingPitchGenerationAdapter()).generate_pitches(\nbackend/tests/test_pitch_generation_service.py:215:        selected_pitch=ExistingSelectedPitchContext