{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_71","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/zsh -lc \"nl -ba backend/app/ai/bedtime_guidelines.py | sed -n '1,220p'\"","aggregated_output":"     1\tfrom __future__ import annotations\n     2\t\n     3\tfrom functools import lru_cache\n     4\t\n     5\tfrom app.models.bedtime_guidelines import (\n     6\t    DEFAULT_BEDTIME_GUIDELINE_PRESET_KEY,\n     7\t    BedtimePromptStage,\n     8\t    normalize_bedtime_guideline_preset_key,\n     9\t)\n    10\t\n    11\t_SHARED_POLICY_LINES: tuple[str, ...] = (\n    12\t    \"Audience preset: Shared Bedtime Default for a broad bedtime read-aloud audience.\",\n    13\t    (\n    14\t        \"Adventure, wonder, discovery, and mild mystery are welcome when the world keeps \"\n    15\t        \"offering visible safety, trustworthy companionship, and a believable path back to calm.\"\n    16\t    ),\n    17\t    (\n    18\t        \"Maximum scare level: brief shivers, uncertainty, wistful mistakes, or soft suspense. \"\n    19\t        \"Never escalate into horror, menace, cruelty, panic spirals, helpless entrapment, or \"\n    20\t        \"grotesque imagery.\"\n    21\t    ),\n    22\t    (\n    23\t        \"Violence avoidance: do not depict assault, graphic injury, weapons use, revenge, \"\n    24\t        \"on-page death, predatory pursuit, or punishment-driven conflict. Resolve problems \"\n    25\t        \"through care, patience, teamwork, cleverness, or emotional honesty.\"\n    26\t    ),\n    27\t    (\n    28\t        \"Emotional repair: after every tense or sad beat, quickly add grounding actions, named \"\n    29\t        \"feelings, supportive relationships, and evidence that the problem is manageable.\"\n    30\t    ),\n    31\t    (\n    32\t        \"Resolution requirement: the ending must land in safety, reconnection, and restful \"\n    33\t        \"release. The final images should invite sleep instead of reopening suspense.\"\n    34\t    ),\n    35\t)\n    36\t\n    37\t_STAGE_SPECIFIC_LINES: dict[BedtimePromptStage, tuple[str, ...]] = {\n    38\t    \"pitch\": (\n    39\t        \"Keep the core conflict curious, tender, or gently urgent rather than perilous.\",\n    40\t        \"Make the repair path legible in the hook or fit note so the bedtime promise is clear.\",\n    41\t    ),\n    42\t    \"character\": (\n    43\t        \"Give the lead a comfort trait and at least one reliable source of support.\",\n    44\t        \"Avoid cruel dynamics, humiliating authority figures, or isolated children with no help.\",\n    45\t    ),\n    46\t    \"beat\": (\n    47\t        (\n    48\t            \"Treat Save-the-Cat low points as tiredness, doubt, sadness, or misread signals \"\n    49\t            \"instead of threat escalation.\"\n    50\t        ),\n    51\t        (\n    52\t            \"Pressure beats should pivot quickly toward reassurance, insight, or renewed \"\n    53\t            \"togetherness.\"\n    54\t        ),\n    55\t    ),\n    56\t    \"composition\": (\n    57\t        (\n    58\t            \"Use calm sensory language, steady pacing, and orienting cues when mystery or \"\n    59\t            \"tension rises.\"\n    60\t        ),\n    61\t        (\n    62\t            \"Avoid shock verbs, nightmare imagery, graphic detail, or cliffhanger endings \"\n    63\t            \"that spike arousal.\"\n    64\t        ),\n    65\t    ),\n    66\t    \"audio\": (\n    67\t        (\n    68\t            \"Narration should sound warm, patient, and emotionally regulated rather than \"\n    69\t            \"theatrical or alarming.\"\n    70\t        ),\n    71\t        (\n    72\t            \"Keep music subordinate to speech clarity and avoid sudden stingers, jump-scare \"\n    73\t            \"phrasing, or aggressive performance cues.\"\n    74\t        ),\n    75\t    ),\n    76\t}\n    77\t\n    78\t\n    79\t@lru_cache(maxsize=None)\n    80\tdef build_bedtime_guidelines_fragment(\n    81\t    *,\n    82\t    stage: BedtimePromptStage,\n    83\t    preset_key: str = DEFAULT_BEDTIME_GUIDELINE_PRESET_KEY,\n    84\t) -> str:\n    85\t    normalized_preset_key = normalize_bedtime_guideline_preset_key(preset_key)\n    86\t    if normalized_preset_key != DEFAULT_BEDTIME_GUIDELINE_PRESET_KEY:\n    87\t        raise ValueError(f\"unsupported bedtime guideline preset key: {normalized_preset_key}\")\n    88\t\n    89\t    lines = [\n    90\t        \"Shared bedtime safety policy:\",\n    91\t        *[f\"- {line}\" for line in _SHARED_POLICY_LINES],\n    92\t        f\"Stage focus for {stage}:\",\n    93\t        *[f\"- {line}\" for line in _STAGE_SPECIFIC_LINES[stage]],\n    94\t    ]\n    95\t    return \"\\n\".join(lines)\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_72","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/zsh -lc \"nl -ba backend/app/models/bedtime_guidelines.py | sed -n '1,220p'\"","aggregated_output":"     1\tfrom __future__ import annotations\n     2\t\n     3\tfrom typing import Literal\n     4\t\n     5\tfrom pydantic import BaseModel, ConfigDict, Field\n     6\t\n     7\tBedtimePromptStage = Literal[\"pitch\", \"character\", \"beat\", \"composition\", \"audio\"]\n     8\tBedtimeAudiencePresetStatus = Literal[\"active\", \"planned\"]\n     9\t\n    10\tDEFAULT_BEDTIME_GUIDELINE_PRESET_KEY = \"shared_bedtime_default\"\n    11\tBEDTIME_PROMPT_STAGES: tuple[BedtimePromptStage, ...] = (\n    12\t    \"pitch\",\n    13\t    \"character\",\n    14\t    \"beat\",\n    15\t    \"composition\",\n    16\t    \"audio\",\n    17\t)\n    18\t\n    19\t\n    20\tclass BedtimeAudiencePresetPlan(BaseModel):\n    21\t    model_config = ConfigDict(extra=\"forbid\", frozen=True)\n    22\t\n    23\t    key: str\n    24\t    label: str\n    25\t    status: BedtimeAudiencePresetStatus\n    26\t    age_band: str\n    27\t    summary: str\n    28\t    prompt_adjustments: list[str] = Field(default_factory=list)\n    29\t\n    30\t\n    31\tBEDTIME_AUDIENCE_PRESET_PLAN: tuple[BedtimeAudiencePresetPlan, ...] = (\n    32\t    BedtimeAudiencePresetPlan(\n    33\t        key=DEFAULT_BEDTIME_GUIDELINE_PRESET_KEY,\n    34\t        label=\"Shared Bedtime Default\",\n    35\t        status=\"active\",\n    36\t        age_band=\"Broad bedtime audience\",\n    37\t        summary=(\n    38\t            \"The current production preset keeps tension gentle enough for a wide bedtime \"\n    39\t            \"read-aloud audience while still allowing adventure, wonder, and mild mystery.\"\n    40\t        ),\n    41\t        prompt_adjustments=[\n    42\t            \"Treat fear as brief uncertainty or wistfulness, not terror or menace.\",\n    43\t            \"Restore visible safety before ending any tense sequence.\",\n    44\t            \"Favor warm, rhythmic language that naturally settles toward sleep.\",\n    45\t        ],\n    46\t    ),\n    47\t    BedtimeAudiencePresetPlan(\n    48\t        key=\"preschool_gentle_3_to_5\",\n    49\t        label=\"Preschool Gentle\",\n    50\t        status=\"planned\",\n    51\t        age_band=\"Ages 3-5\",\n    52\t        summary=(\n    53\t            \"Future preset that further lowers the tension ceiling, shortens uncertainty \"\n    54\t            \"windows, and relies on very explicit reassurance.\"\n    55\t        ),\n    56\t        prompt_adjustments=[\n    57\t            \"Reduce abstract peril and keep support figures present almost constantly.\",\n    58\t            \"Use simpler emotional naming and faster repair beats after surprises.\",\n    59\t        ],\n    60\t    ),\n    61\t    BedtimeAudiencePresetPlan(\n    62\t        key=\"early_reader_calm_6_to_8\",\n    63\t        label=\"Early Reader Calm Adventure\",\n    64\t        status=\"planned\",\n    65\t        age_band=\"Ages 6-8\",\n    66\t        summary=(\n    67\t            \"Future preset that preserves calm mystery and quest momentum while allowing a \"\n    68\t            \"slightly wider emotional range than the preschool track.\"\n    69\t        ),\n    70\t        prompt_adjustments=[\n    71\t            \"Allow slightly longer puzzle-solving stretches as long as safe exits remain visible.\",\n    72\t            \"Keep setbacks tender and resolvable through teamwork rather than confrontation.\",\n    73\t        ],\n    74\t    ),\n    75\t    BedtimeAudiencePresetPlan(\n    76\t        key=\"older_kids_soft_mystery_9_to_12\",\n    77\t        label=\"Older Kids Soft Mystery\",\n    78\t        status=\"planned\",\n    79\t        age_band=\"Ages 9-12\",\n    80\t        summary=(\n    81\t            \"Future preset that supports richer mystery structure and more reflective low \"\n    82\t            \"points without abandoning the bedtime emotional landing.\"\n    83\t        ),\n    84\t        prompt_adjustments=[\n    85\t            \"Permit more layered ambiguity while avoiding horror imagery or hopeless despair.\",\n    86\t            \"Use reflective emotional repair rather than flattening every scene into cheerfulness.\",\n    87\t        ],\n    88\t    ),\n    89\t)\n    90\t\n    91\t_ACTIVE_BEDTIME_GUIDELINE_PRESET_KEYS = frozenset(\n    92\t    preset.key for preset in BEDTIME_AUDIENCE_PRESET_PLAN if preset.status == \"active\"\n    93\t)\n    94\t\n    95\t\n    96\tdef normalize_bedtime_guideline_preset_key(value: str | None) -> str:\n    97\t    if value is None:\n    98\t        return DEFAULT_BEDTIME_GUIDELINE_PRESET_KEY\n    99\t\n   100\t    normalized = value.strip()\n   101\t    if not normalized:\n   102\t        return DEFAULT_BEDTIME_GUIDELINE_PRESET_KEY\n   103\t\n   104\t    if normalized not in _ACTIVE_BEDTIME_GUIDELINE_PRESET_KEYS:\n   105\t        raise ValueError(f\"unsupported bedtime guideline preset key: {normalized}\")\n   106\t\n   107\t    return normalized\n   108\t\n   109\t\n   110\tdef get_bedtime_audience_preset_plan() -> tuple[BedtimeAudiencePresetPlan, ...]:\n   111\t    return BEDTIME_AUDIENCE_PRESET_PLAN\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_70","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/zsh -lc \"nl -ba docs/bedtime-guidelines.md | sed -n '1,240p'\"","aggregated_output":"     1\t# Bedtime Safety and Content Guidelines\n     2\t\n     3\tStoryteller needs one shared definition of \"bedtime-safe\" so planning, writing, and narration do\n     4\tnot drift into harsher territory as the workflow advances. This file documents the current product\n     5\trules and the backend abstractions that carry them into prompts.\n     6\t\n     7\t## Core Promise\n     8\t\n     9\tBedtime-safe does not mean flat or boring. The product should still support:\n    10\t\n    11\t- wonder\n    12\t- gentle adventure\n    13\t- mild mystery\n    14\t- emotional growth\n    15\t- meaningful low points that resolve into safety\n    16\t\n    17\tThe constraint is emotional intensity, not imagination. A good bedtime story can move, surprise,\n    18\tand transform, but it should still guide the listener toward rest.\n    19\t\n    20\t## Current Safety Rules\n    21\t\n    22\t### Maximum scare level\n    23\t\n    24\t- The ceiling is brief shivers, uncertainty, wistful mistakes, or soft suspense.\n    25\t- Tension can rise, but it should remain readable and buffered by visible safety cues.\n    26\t- Do not cross into horror, menace, panic spirals, helpless entrapment, predatory pursuit, or\n    27\t  grotesque imagery.\n    28\t\n    29\t### Violence avoidance\n    30\t\n    31\t- Do not depict assault, graphic injury, on-page death, revenge, punishment-driven conflict, or\n    32\t  weapon-centered action.\n    33\t- Avoid villains or threats whose primary function is to terrify the child listener.\n    34\t- Prefer problems that can be solved through care, patience, teamwork, cleverness, repair, or\n    35\t  emotional honesty.\n    36\t\n    37\t### Emotional repair after tension\n    38\t\n    39\t- After each tense or sad turn, quickly re-establish grounding through companionship, named\n    40\t  feelings, familiar rituals, or other signs that the problem is manageable.\n    41\t- Characters may worry, doubt themselves, or feel briefly lost, but they should not remain\n    42\t  emotionally stranded for long.\n    43\t- Save-the-Cat low points should feel tender or reflective, not traumatic.\n    44\t\n    45\t### Reassuring resolution\n    46\t\n    47\t- Endings must visibly restore safety, connection, and calm.\n    48\t- The last movement of the story should downshift into rest rather than reopening suspense.\n    49\t- Final images should feel tucked-in, settled, and sleep-compatible.\n    50\t\n    51\t### Audio-specific posture\n    52\t\n    53\t- Narration should sound warm, patient, and emotionally regulated.\n    54\t- Music should support the voice rather than dominate it.\n    55\t- Avoid performance choices that feel like jump scares, villain turns, or sudden intensity spikes.\n    56\t\n    57\t## How The Backend Reuses These Rules\n    58\t\n    59\tThe reusable backend source of truth lives in:\n    60\t\n    61\t- [`backend/app/models/bedtime_guidelines.py`](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/app/models/bedtime_guidelines.py)\n    62\t- [`backend/app/ai/bedtime_guidelines.py`](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/app/ai/bedtime_guidelines.py)\n    63\t\n    64\tThe split is deliberate:\n    65\t\n    66\t- `backend/app/models/bedtime_guidelines.py` stores the preset key, active-vs-planned audience\n    67\t  preset plan, and validation helpers.\n    68\t- `backend/app/ai/bedtime_guidelines.py` renders stage-specific prompt fragments for `pitch`,\n    69\t  `character`, `beat`, `composition`, and `audio`.\n    70\t\n    71\tThe live prompt builders currently inject the shared fragment into:\n    72\t\n    73\t- [`backend/app/ai/pitch_generation.py`](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/app/ai/pitch_generation.py)\n    74\t- [`backend/app/ai/character_generation.py`](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/app/ai/character_generation.py)\n    75\t- [`backend/app/ai/beat_sheet_generation.py`](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/app/ai/beat_sheet_generation.py)\n    76\t\n    77\tThat keeps the bedtime rules centralized instead of rewording them independently in each template.\n    78\t\n    79\t## Audience-Age Preset Plan\n    80\t\n    81\tThe first implementation stays simple: the product uses one active preset,\n    82\t`shared_bedtime_default`, for a broad bedtime read-aloud audience. The backend also stores a plan\n    83\tfor future expansion so later prompts can add age-aware defaults without another structural\n    84\trewrite.\n    85\t\n    86\tPlanned follow-on presets:\n    87\t\n    88\t- `preschool_gentle_3_to_5`\n    89\t  Bias toward extremely fast reassurance, simpler emotional naming, and near-constant visible\n    90\t  support.\n    91\t- `early_reader_calm_6_to_8`\n    92\t  Allow slightly longer mystery/problem-solving loops while keeping setbacks tender and solvable\n    93\t  through teamwork.\n    94\t- `older_kids_soft_mystery_9_to_12`\n    95\t  Allow more layered ambiguity and reflection while still rejecting horror imagery and hopeless\n    96\t  endings.\n    97\t\n    98\tThe pipeline hook is already in place through `bedtime_guideline_preset_key` on the prompt context\n    99\tmodels. The current validator only accepts the active preset, which keeps production behavior\n   100\tdeterministic until the product explicitly decides to expose age selection.\n   101\t\n   102\t## Practical Usage\n   103\t\n   104\tWhen a new stage prompt is added, reuse the same abstraction instead of copying policy text:\n   105\t\n   106\t```python\n   107\tfrom app.ai.bedtime_guidelines import build_bedtime_guidelines_fragment\n   108\t\n   109\tfragment = build_bedtime_guidelines_fragment(\n   110\t    stage=\"composition\",\n   111\t    preset_key=\"shared_bedtime_default\",\n   112\t)\n   113\t```\n   114\t\n   115\tThat call returns the shared bedtime policy plus stage-specific instructions for the requested\n   116\tpipeline step. Composition and audio fragments already exist even though those prompt templates are\n   117\tnot live in the repository yet.\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
