{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_76","type":"agent_message","text":"Implemented the bedtime-safety policy end to end. The shared policy registry lives in [bedtime_guidelines.py](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/app/models/bedtime_guidelines.py) and the reusable prompt fragment builder lives in [bedtime_guidelines.py](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/app/ai/bedtime_guidelines.py). I wired that fragment into the live pitch, character, and beat prompt renderers, added the future-facing `bedtime_guideline_preset_key` hook to the prompt contexts/services, bumped the affected prompt versions, and documented the product rules plus age-preset plan in [bedtime-guidelines.md](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/bedtime-guidelines.md).\n\nVerification is complete: `ruff check` passed, and `pytest backend/tests/test_bedtime_guidelines.py backend/tests/test_pitch_generation_service.py backend/tests/test_character_generation_service.py backend/tests/test_beat_sheet_generation_service.py backend/tests/test_session_beat_sheet_service.py backend/tests/test_session_service.py -q` passed with `49 passed in 1.87s`. No browser or screenshot checks were run because this was a backend/docs prompt-policy change. I created checkpoint commit `61dad11` and wrote the required reviewer summary to [summary.md](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/.yolopilot/runs/20260331T205548_storyteller_prompt_pack/52_bedtime_safety_and_content_guidelines/summary.md). The only remaining uncommitted files are the run-generated `.yolopilot` log/status files."}}
